<TITLE> Thunderstorm kills 3 in Bhola </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhola, June 4 (bdnews24.com)  A severe thunderstorm tore through Nil Kamal Union in Bhola Monday morning, leaving three people dead and four injured in the village of Char Nurul Amin. The three who died were carpenters Nurul Islam, 40, Ilias, 36, and Nesar Uddin (age unknown), according to Upazila Nirbahi Officer Mostafa Kamal. The carpenters were struck by lightning at about 9:30 in the morning when they were at work. They died on the spot, according to Kamal. The four injured were taken to Charfashion Upazila Health Complex for treatment. The storm also caused massive damage to the standing crops in the area, said the Nil Kamal Union Parishad chairman. bdnews24.co
